transcript.text: Open your file in Adobe Illustrator.
Select Pen tool to draw a path.
Create a path with your preferred shape.
Copy the path and paste it in a new document.
You can use Shortcut Control plus N to open a new document and Control plus V to paste the path in new document.
Select Artboard tool to resize the page according to the path size.
Go to preset menu and select fit to selected art.
Select the path and save as it in SVG format.
Select SVG from the drop down menu.
Click on Save button.
Check settings for SVG format, Save file in PDF format.
Select PDF from the drop down menu.
Click on Save button.
Your document is saved at desktop.
Open the document using Edit with Notepad++.
Copy this path to paste it into Custom Properties window.
In PDF Block plugin.
Open your PDF file with Adobe Acrobat.
Click on PD Flip Blocks menu to activate the PD Flip Block tool.
Draw one block using PD Flip block Pledge in.
While drawing this block, consider the below points.
One block should cover highest left of path.
Two blocks should cover highest right of path.
Three blocks should cover highest bottom of path.
Four blocks should cover highest top of path.
Match right, left, bottom and top sides perfectly with the borders of path.
Select the type of block.
Here it is image block.
Set block properties using property window.
Set fit method and position from this properties window.
Add default image here.
Also add custom prog mount.
Since this is an image block, set this block at highest of four sides.
Now PDF file is ready for upload.
Save file from file menu.
